hopobject.body: Where's the nearest cash machine? online pharmacy harassment Such ideas, however, are vehemently opposed by the trade unions – meaning there is little hope of Miliband being able to change Labour’s current policy of taking the NHS back to a state-only system of “preferred providers” to deliver hospital care. But the voters are wising up: not only to Labour’s past mistakes, but its lack of new ideas on how to fix things. For that reason, today may well be the beginning of the end for Labour’s comfortable monopoly on being trusted to run our most valued public service.
